# EventEase: Visual Architecture & System Flows

This document provides a high-level visual representation of the EventEase AI Platform's internal architecture and user journey.

## 🏗️ System Architecture

```mermaid
graph TD
    User((User/Student))
    Organizer((Event Organizer))
    
    subgraph Frontend [React Frontend]
        UI[UI Components - Shadcn/Tailwind]
        State[Redux Toolkit Store]
        Router[React Router 7]
    end
    
    subgraph Backend [Express Backend]
        API[Express REST API]
        Auth[JWT Authentication]
        Controller[Business Logic Controllers]
    end
    
    subgraph AI_Engine [AI & Data]
        Groq[Groq AI SDK]
        DB[(MongoDB Atlas)]
    end
    
    User <--> Router
    Organizer <--> Router
    Router <--> UI
    UI <--> State
    State <--> API
    API <--> Auth
    API <--> Controller
    Controller <--> DB
    Controller <--> Groq
```

## 🔄 User Discovery Flow

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant U as Student
    participant F as Frontend
    participant B as Backend
    participant AI as Groq AI

    U->>F: Visit Discovery
    F->>B: GET /api/events
    B-->>F: List of Events
    F->>U: Show Generic Events
    
    U->>F: Login
    F->>B: POST /api/auth/login
    B-->>F: JWT Token & Profile
    
    F->>B: GET /api/recommendations
    B->>AI: Fetch Personalized Picks (Interests)
    AI-->>B: Recommended Event IDs
    B-->>F: Curated Events
    F->>U: Show "Recommended For You"
```

